This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it discusses checkpointing in stream processing systems, which are often distributed and parallel. It may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it presents a theoretical framework for determining optimal parameter settings. The paper also considers failure rates and restart costs, which are related to system dynamics and control, making the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category a likely candidate. Additionally, the paper may belong to the Performance (cs.PF) sub-category as it discusses the efficiency of checkpointing systems. Finally, the Networked and Internet-based Systems (cs.NI) sub-category is a possibility as stream processing systems often involve networked and internet-based communication.
